profile_positions.description:
Responsible for defining and implementing the Data Management processes at Canon EMEA. Playing a key role in improvement projects, helping the stakeholders to the next level of professionalism by creating more valuable insights from available data and by acting on.

• Plan, coordinate and execute Data Management initiatives across the organization, such as Data Quality and Data Governance;
• Support MDM system setup; Analyze gap in processes, systems or databases and make recommendations for further improvement, development, standardization or simplification, based on the business priorities;
• Communicate business requirements effectively and transform into changes, and provide up-to-date Work Instruction;
• Build or expand relationship with MDM user communities in Functions/BU’s, and ensure they are in alignment with the MDM objectives;
• Demonstrate in-depth understanding of End-to-End business processes which use Master Data;
